lead_paragraph: African soccer leaders elected Guinea's Almamy Kabele Camara and Ghana's Kwesi Nyantakyi on Thursday to represent the continent on the expanded 36-member FIFA Council.

headline.print_headline: African Duo Voted Onto FIFA Council by CAF
